Discharge Remarks: SxS measurement notes: ADCP could not detect flow beneath slush horizon at panel locations where slush was present. Used Price Meter 6-429 on ice-rod assembly to measure ice/slush/velocity at some locations. Trimble and HFC 3.1.1 used to measure velocity - this information entered into SXS software as manual verticals... SXS software has bug such that if total depths are entered manually, the software displays the channel profile incorrectly. Instead effective depths were entered - discharge is computed accurately. Mmnt end time is incorrect in SXS mmnt file (manual vertical times were not used by the software (??) to calculate end time, so mmnt end time is from HFC file. Pitch/roll spikes observed in all transects due to high velocity flow and unstable ADCP bracket/mast. ADCP transducer depth reduced from 0.4 m to 0.3 m for transects 002,003 to mitigate vibration induced pitch/roll spikes. Operated boat at slower speed (allowing more drift d/s) for transects 002,003. Extrap indicated exponent: 0.2595 and power/power for top/bottom extrap method - modified field config accordingly. Transects 002 and 003 subsectioned to remove portion where boat drifted back towards centre (resulting in incorrect bed contour). Reduced shore pings for subsectioned transects. Only the second loop test was applied (first loop test average boat speed >0.7 m/s).  Poor GPS, so BT used for measurement reference. High pitch and roll observed in TR 000, 001 due fast and turbulent flow and high transducer depth. Slowed boat speed and reduced transducer depth for TR 002, 003; changes had positive results (minimized vibration). Extrap indicated Exp: 0.2595 and power/power extrapolation for a -1.57% diff. ~5% directional bias observed. Only TRK GPS availale, so BT loop corrected used.
